T1  - A Markov model of heteroskedasticity, risk, and learning in the stock market
AU  - Turner, Christopher M.
AU  - Startz, Richard
AU  - Nelson, Charles R.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 25
IS  - 1
SP  - 3
EP  - 22
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/11/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(89)90094-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X89900949
AB  - We examine a variety of models in which the variance of a portfolio's excess return depends on a state variable generated by a first-order Markov process. A model in which the state is known to economic agents is estimated. It suggests that the mean excess return moves inversely with the level of risk. We then estimate a model in which agents are uncertain of the state. The estimates indicate that agents are consistently surprised by high-variance periods, so there is a negative correlation between movements in volatility and in excess returns.
ER  - 

